{{Quote|Hey, you're the married one. Find me a human girl with Malla's brains and silky hair and maybe I'll consider it.|Han Solo, to Chewbacca|<ref name="PSFB" />}}
'''Mallatobuck''', also known as '''Malla''', was the [[Marriage|wife]] of [[Chewbacca]], the [[Wookiee]] co-[[pilot]] of the [[Corellian]] [[smuggler]] [[Han Solo]]. During the [[Imperial Era]], Malla and her [[Chewbacca's family|family]] were [[Slavery|enslaved]] by the [[Galactic Empire]]. She was separated from her husband Chewbacca and her son [[Lumpawaroo]]. Following the [[Liberation of Kashyyyk]], she was reunited with her family.

==Biography==
Malla was the wife of [[Chewbacca]] and the mother of [[Lumpawaroo]]. During the [[Imperial Era]], Malla and her [[Chewbacca's family|family]] were enslaved by the Empire. She and her son were put in an [[Galactic Empire|Imperial]] [[Slavery|slave]] camp on [[Kashyyyk]].<ref name="AB Update">''[[Star Wars: Absolutely Everything You Need to Know, Updated and Expanded]]''</ref> At some point, Malla was separated from her son Lumpawaroo, who became a child slave in [[Commandant]] [[Dessard]]'s camp on the slopes of [[Mount Arayakyak]].<ref name="Empire's End" /> Her husband Chewbacca ended up as a slave on the planet [[Mimban]] until he was rescued by [[Han Solo]], a renegade Imperial [[Swamp trooper|Mud trooper]].<ref name="Solo">''[[Solo: A Star Wars Story]]''</ref>

During the [[Galactic Civil War]] that pitted the [[Galactic Empire]] against the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic]], Chewbacca was traveling with Solo, away from Malla<ref name="PSFB" /> and the rest of his family on Kashyyyk.<ref name="TFAVD">''[[Star Wars: The Force Awakens: The Visual Dictionary]]''</ref> Following the [[Liberation of Kashyyyk]] from the Empire's grasp, Chewbacca finally reunited with his wife and son.<ref name="AB Update" />

==Personality and traits==
Malla was a [[Gender|female]]<ref name="PSFB" /> [[Wookiee]]<ref name="Tales from Vandor" /> who was married to Chewbacca<ref name="PSFB" /> and the mother of [[Lumpawaroo]].<ref name="AB Update" /> According to Solo, she was intelligent and had [[hair]] resembling silk.<ref name="PSFB" />

==Behind the scenes==
Mallatobuck was first mentioned in ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[canon]] in the [[2015]] young readers novel ''[[A New Hope: The Princess, the Scoundrel, and the Farm Boy]]'', a retelling of [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']] written by [[Alexandra Bracken]].<ref name="PSFB" /> Malla was created for ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]'', a [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] TV movie released in [[1978]].<ref name="Holiday Special">''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]''</ref>

